I think this distasteful obsession with performative religious polemics in the right-wing always comes as a cope for not being able to openly talk about race. E.g. is the real problem for him that Mauritanians are Muslim and not something else that is just as obvious to everyone?

Avoiding the one forbidden topic always leads to even more bizarre forms of cruelty like how ICE performed hysterectomies on Mexican girls and the Israeli gov chemically castrated a bunch of Ethiopian women. They couldn't openly deport them, so they ruined innocent lives instead.

Similarly you see attempts to e.g. ban burqas or mosques in public and religious provocations like that French newspapers blaspheming against a people's religion in an obviously repulsive way, because they are unable to directly attack them as a group. Cope leads to cruelty.
